---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Akrity.Work - Cheat Sheet"
  description="A quick guide to MDX syntax and custom components for Akrity.Work"
  pubDate={new Date('March 16 2025')}
  heroImage="/blog-placeholder-about.jpg"
>
  <style>
    .syntax {
      background-color: #2c2c2c;
      padding: 0.5em 1em;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
      color: #f4f4f4;
      display: block;
      margin: 0.5em 0;
      white-space: pre-wrap;
    }
    .notice {
      background-color: #fff3cd;
      border: 1px solid #ffeeba;
      padding: 1em;
      border-radius: 4px;
      margin-bottom: 2em;
      color: #856404;
    }
    p {
      margin-bottom: 1em;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    h2 {
      margin-top: 2em;
      margin-bottom: 1em;
      color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
    }
    .feature-section {
      margin-bottom: 2em;
    }
  </style>

  <h1>Welcome to Akrity.Work - Cheat Sheet</h1>

  <div class="notice">
    <p><strong>Notice:</strong> In all custom components, values are separated by commas <span class="syntax">Task: Title, Assignee, Status</span>Type the syntax carefully to avoid errors!</p>
    <p>A newline must be added above and below each component for smooth rendering in your MDX file.</p>
  </div>

  <p>
    New to Akrity.Work? This page covers the basics of MDX and our custom components. Syntax is shown in <span class="syntax">styled boxes</span> below each description—use these to write posts, track tasks, and share updates with the team!
  </p>

  <h2>Native MDX Features</h2>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Headings: Organize your content with titles and sections.</p>
    <span class="syntax"># Main Title
## Subsection</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Paragraphs: Write regular text, separated by line breaks.</p>
    <span class="syntax">First paragraph.
Second paragraph.</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Bold & Italic: Emphasize key words.</p>
    <span class="syntax">**Bold this**
*Italicize that*</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Lists (Unordered): Create bullet points.</p>
    <span class="syntax">- Item one
- Item two
- Item three</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Lists (Ordered): Make numbered lists.</p>
    <span class="syntax">1. First step
2. Second step
3. Third step</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Links: Add clickable URLs.</p>
    <span class="syntax">[Visit Akrity.Work](https://akrity.work)</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Blockquotes: Quote someone or highlight text.</p>
    <span class="syntax">> This is a quote.</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Horizontal Rules: Add a divider line.</p>
    <span class="syntax">---</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Code Blocks: Display code with highlighting.</p>
    <span class="syntax">```javascript
console.log('Hello');
```</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Images: Embed images with alt text (use real paths).</p>
    <span class="syntax">![Dashboard](/blog-placeholder-1.jpg)</span>
  </div>

  <h2>Custom Components</h2>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Meeting: Log a team meeting.</p>
    <span class="syntax">Meeting: Attendees, Time, Agenda, Outcome</span>
    <span class="syntax">Meeting: Prathamesh and Rahul, 4-5 PM, Backend Sync, Resolved Issues</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Task: Track a task’s progress.</p>
    <span class="syntax">Task: Title, Assignee, Status</span>
    <span class="syntax">Task: Fix login bug, Rahul, In Progress</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Blocker: Report an issue.</p>
    <span class="syntax">Blocker: Description, ReportedBy</span>
    <span class="syntax">Blocker: API downtime, Prathamesh</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>ActionItem: Assign a task with a due date.</p>
    <span class="syntax">ActionItem: Description, Assignee, DueDate</span>
    <span class="syntax">ActionItem: Update README, Rahul, 2025-03-20</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>StandUpSummary: Recap a stand-up meeting.</p>
    <span class="syntax">StandUpSummary: Date, Team, Summary</span>
    <span class="syntax">StandUpSummary: 2025-03-14, Backend Team, Resolved API issues</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Progress: Show task progress.</p>
    <span class="syntax">Progress: Task, Percentage, Notes</span>
    <span class="syntax">Progress: Frontend redesign, 75%, Waiting on feedback</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Callout: Highlight a tip or note.</p>
    <span class="syntax">Callout: Type, Content</span>
    <span class="syntax">Callout: tip, Test this locally first</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>CodeSnippet: Display code in a styled box.</p>
    <span class="syntax">CodeSnippet: Language, Code</span>
    <span class="syntax">CodeSnippet: javascript, console.log('Hello');</span>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-section">
    <p>Image: Embed an image with a caption.</p>
    <span class="syntax">Image: Src, Alt, Caption</span>
    <span class="syntax">Image: /blog-placeholder-1.jpg, Dashboard, New design preview</span>
  </div>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <p>
    Add a blank line before and after each component for smooth rendering. Use commas to separate values in components, keeping extra spaces minimal. See <span class="syntax">new-post.mdx</span> in <span class="syntax">src/content/blog/</span> for a full example!
  </p>

  <div class="feature-section">
  <p>Milestone: Celebrate achievements with a roadmap style.</p>
  <span class="syntax">Milestone: Date, Title, Details</span>
  <span class="syntax">Milestone: 2025-03-17, App Launch, Released v1.0</span>
</div>

<div class="feature-section">
  <p>Shoutout: Recognize team members with a bubble.</p>
  <span class="syntax">Shoutout: Person, Reason</span>
  <span class="syntax">Shoutout: Rahul, Fixed login bug in record time</span>
</div>

<div class="feature-section">
  <p>Idea: Brainstorm with priority tags.</p>
  <span class="syntax">Idea: Concept, Priority, Notes</span>
  <span class="syntax">Idea: Dark mode, High, Needs design input</span>
</div>
</Layout>